nodes.title: Note ‚Üì
widgets_values:
‚Äî <system_msg> defines the assistent profile and instruction 
‚Äî <max_tokens> sets the maximum length of the output
‚Äî <temperature> controls randomness of answers, increasing variety and creativity, in exchange for accuracy
‚Äî <top_p> impacts output length and also balances creativity/accuracy
‚Äî <top_k> caps the amount of tokens considered for each generated token to the k-amount most likely options
‚Äî <frequency_penalty> discourages repetitiveness
‚Äî <presence_penalty> encourages a wider scope of token consideration
‚Äî <repeat_penalty> should do the same as <frequency_penalty>

nodes.title: Note ‚Üì
widgets_values:
‚Äî <ckpt_name> is where you select your local LLM of choice
‚Äî <max_ctx> defines the amount of tokens used as a memory. If lowered too much, the LLM would "forget" about the task before completing it.
   ‚Üí 2048 works fine
‚Äî <gpu_layers> layers of the LLM to be handled by the gpu's VRAM
   ‚Üí higher is better/faster
   ‚Üí if you run out of memory, lower that number, if you have enough VRAM you can increase it to speed up processing.
‚Äî <n_threads> the amount of threads your CPU handles at once. Leaving it at the default of 8 works fine.

widgets_values:
Hotkey:

  1: base, image selection, & noise injection

  3: lora, controlnet parameters, & adv model parameters

Workflow Control:
  All switches in any Workflow panel take effect in realtime.
  All switches in any Select panel also affect sub workflow, but don't take effect in realtime, which needs preprocessing.

  Preprocessing needs to be executed before actural generation for switches in Select or Parameters panels to control the sub workflow. 
  Pre-process Pannel: Alternatively, you can preprocess manually by setting the corresponding switches in the Pre-process Pannel to the same state as in the Parameters Pannel, which does not need a Pre-Queue Prompt.
